Speaker 1: Hello, Mr. Newton. Yeah, I'm here. Yeah, yeah, so I was talking to my manager for—

Speaker 2: Approval. So basically, he was telling me that the principal wants that, you know—

Speaker 1: You can't use up to half of the medicine but not the whole medicine. If you don't—

Speaker 2: Work in a work is really is willing to split the cost, like, you know, we can't—

Speaker 1: Give you 50% back, but because you have no pill, you have nothing to return.

Speaker 2: Okay, no. Yeah, you know what? I just won't deal with you guys. You know, you guys—

Speaker 1: Enjoy the damn money. Okay, I don't need anything, you know. I want, you know, I—

Speaker 2: Paid full cost for them. How do you think you're gonna find out if they work if—

Speaker 1: You don't take the damn pills? That makes no sense.
